1: Source Code

Wrote a basic python code for app and it's requirement file

2:  Dockerfile

Wrote a Dockerfile to build a image of the python app


3. Run Semgrep locally to verify

pip install semgrep
semgrep --config=auto --json --output reports/semgrep.json path/to/your/code


4. Run Trivy locally

curl -sfL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/aquasecurity/trivy/main/contrib/install.sh | sh


5. Run Docker Bench Security

docker run --rm --platform linux/amd64 --net host --pid host --userns host --cap-add audit_control \
  -v /etc:/etc:ro \
  -v /usr/bin/containerd:/usr/bin/containerd:ro \
  -v /usr/bin/runc:/usr/bin/runc:ro \
  -v /usr/lib/systemd:/usr/lib/systemd:ro \
  -v /var/lib:/var/lib:ro \
  -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock:ro \
  docker/docker-bench-security > reports/docker-bench.txt
